Yorkshire Ripper Peter Sutcliffe has spent three decades in Broadmoor for the killings of 13 women . 
  He is said to be being moved to a low security Priory unit set in Berkshire woodland . 
  Families of his victims are furious at plans to move him from high security hospital . 
  Sutcliffe is currently said to enjoy a cushy lifestyle in jail eating chocolate and watching TV . 
  He has expressed remorse for his crimes and said he no longer hears 'voices from God'